.TH PI-DOCTOR 1 "June 2026" "pi-doctor 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pi-doctor \- read-only Raspberry Pi diagnostics
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pi-doctor
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.I COMMAND
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pi-doctor
checks common Raspberry Pi support issues without changing the host system. It
reports board identity, kernel and distribution metadata, firmware throttling
signals, thermal state, boot configuration drift, GPIO tooling, camera
detection, and Python environment state.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B check
Run the full diagnostic probe set.
.TP
.B explain throttling
Explain firmware throttling and thermal diagnostics.
.TP
.B explain config
Explain Raspberry Pi boot configuration diagnostics.
.TP
.B explain python
Explain Python environment diagnostics.
.TP
.B doctor camera
Run focused camera diagnostics.
.TP
.B doctor gpio
Run focused GPIO diagnostics.
.TP
.B support-bundle
Create a diagnostic bundle. Bundles are sanitized by default and include a
manifest with SHA-256 hashes.
.TP
.B completions SHELL
Generate shell completion scripts.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --json
Emit JSON output for
.B check.
.TP
.B --quiet
Use compact human output.
.TP
.B --verbose
Use verbose human output.
.TP
.B --no-color
Disable color in human output.
.TP
.B --timeout SECONDS
Set the per-command probe timeout.
.TP
.B support-bundle --output DIR
Write the bundle under DIR instead of the current directory.
.TP
.B support-bundle --dry-run
Show exactly which files would be collected without writing a bundle.
.TP
.B support-bundle --include-sensitive --acknowledge-sensitive-data
Disable redaction for expert support cases. This may include hostnames, paths,
serial numbers, URLs, tokens, and raw command output.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show command help.
.TP
.B -V, --version
Show the package version.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The
.B check
command exits with 0 for healthy, 1 for warning, 2 for degraded, and 3 for
critical status. Unexpected runtime failures exit with 4.
.SH SEE ALSO
Project documentation is installed under
.IR /usr/share/doc/pi-doctor/ .
